    {
      "agency": "City of Garden Grove (FAQ)",
      "time_iso": "2026-05-30T00:00:00Z",
      "text": "All evacuation orders related to the hazardous materials incident have been lifted. Orange County health officials have confirmed there are no air quality or other health concerns in the area. Public safety and health agencies confirmed there was no release of chemicals that would warrant specific cleaning or safety precautions for residents. The safety zone around the involved tank has been reduced to 150 feet.",
      "source_url": "https://ggcity.org/hazmat-incident/faq"
    },
    {
      "agency": "OCFA Deputy Incident Commander Mike Yeun",
      "time_iso": "2026-05-30T17:00:00Z",
      "text": "We will work with Orange County Health, and the EPA will work with the company on the removal of the waste.",
